        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued September 10 at 2:36AM CDT by NWS Amarillo TX</headline>
        <description>At 236 AM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking strong thunderstorms along
a line extending from 12 miles north of Boise City to near Griggs.
Movement was east at 20 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and half inch hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Texhoma, Keyes, Eva, Griggs, and Sturgis.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with these storms and may lead
to localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
